1
00:00:08,541 --> 00:00:10,375
♪

2
00:00:10,458 --> 00:00:11,666
[HINOMARU]
Don't move sideways!

3
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:12,625
Forward!

4
00:00:12,708 --> 00:00:14,625
[BOTH grunt]

5
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:17,166
[CHIHIRO]
Another strike!

6
00:00:17,250 --> 00:00:19,291
[HINOMARU] I can see
my goal in front of me!

7
00:00:19,375 --> 00:00:22,583
An adversary, on the cusp
of turning yokozuna!

8
00:00:22,666 --> 00:00:24,708
I'm willing to risk everything,

9
00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:28,000
even my life, for victory!

10
00:00:31,750 --> 00:00:33,125
Heads together.

11
00:00:33,208 --> 00:00:34,500
Both hands on your belt.

12
00:00:35,625 --> 00:00:37,083
I can see the end,

13
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:39,583
and this technique
will get me there!

14
00:00:39,666 --> 00:00:41,375
[KUZE]
I see what you're doing,

15
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,500
and I won't give you
a chance to start.

16
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:48,041
This right overhand grip
was taught to me by my father.

17
00:00:48,125 --> 00:00:49,916
It defines my destiny.

18
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,083
[HINOMARU]
Don't hesitate.

19
00:00:51,166 --> 00:00:53,250
[KUZE]
Just one error.

20
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:54,958
[BOTH]
And I'll lose!

21
00:02:26,458 --> 00:02:29,791
[CROWD cheering]

22
00:02:30,958 --> 00:02:32,208
[grunts]

23
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:35,458
[straining]

24
00:02:40,916 --> 00:02:42,291
They're equals.

25
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:43,625
Deadlock.

26
00:02:43,708 --> 00:02:44,833
Neither can move.

27
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:50,500
[KUZE] My father
once told me something.

28
00:02:50,583 --> 00:02:53,041
Yokozunas are solitary.

29
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:54,791
There's no one ahead of them.

30
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:56,333
No signs.

31
00:02:56,416 --> 00:02:58,750
Nothing to serve as a guide.

32
00:03:00,625 --> 00:03:02,583
[ANNOUNCER on TV]
And he's forced out!

33
00:03:02,666 --> 00:03:05,041
The yokozuna has been defeated!

34
00:03:05,125 --> 00:03:08,291
Kaoruyama scores a major upset
by forcing his opponent out!

35
00:03:08,375 --> 00:03:10,583
He lost?
Your poor dad.

36
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:14,500
[KUZE] Whether he was
victorious or not,

37
00:03:14,583 --> 00:03:16,625
he never showed emotion.

38
00:03:16,708 --> 00:03:19,625
Still, I could sense
the bloodlust in him,

39
00:03:19,708 --> 00:03:21,083
and it unnerved me.

40
00:03:22,166 --> 00:03:24,041
I strove to be a good son.

41
00:03:24,125 --> 00:03:27,166
So I'd never interfere
with his competitions.

42
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:28,958
As for sumo,

43
00:03:29,041 --> 00:03:30,291
my father neither encouraged

44
00:03:30,375 --> 00:03:32,541
nor discouraged me
from participating.

45
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,416
Perhaps I followed
in his footsteps

46
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:38,250
only as a means of showing
the respect I had for him.

47
00:03:39,375 --> 00:03:41,041
I knew the path
wouldn't be easy.

48
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:43,708
Even when he was
bruised and beaten,

49
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:45,625
he continued fighting.

50
00:03:46,875 --> 00:03:48,875
As the son of a yokozuna,

51
00:03:48,958 --> 00:03:50,875
I knew people
treated me differently.

52
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:54,958
It was my duty to follow
in my father's footsteps.

53
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:57,875
To honor his name
and reach his title.

54
00:03:57,958 --> 00:04:01,708
I had to transform,
to become stronger.

55
00:04:01,791 --> 00:04:03,333
As I chased after my goal,

56
00:04:03,416 --> 00:04:06,625
I never once viewed sumo
as something I should enjoy.

57
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:10,666
♪

58
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,416
You're stopping now?

59
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:16,333
♪

60
00:04:16,416 --> 00:04:18,666
[MAN 1] That boy puts
the others to shame.

61
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:20,583
Did you see how stoic he is?

62
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:22,458
[MAN 2] Must be
the yokozuna blood in him.

63
00:04:22,541 --> 00:04:24,083
He's not the same
as the rest of us.

64
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:25,541
Makes me jealous.

65
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:28,166
[KUZE]
Right.

66
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:30,958
This must be the solitude
my father spoke of.

67
00:04:31,041 --> 00:04:33,333
Which means I must be following
the right path.

68
00:04:33,416 --> 00:04:38,500
Even if no one else understands,
even if I have to go it alone,

69
00:04:38,583 --> 00:04:40,916
I'll seek what
my father attained.

70
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,791
A state of a yokozuna.

71
00:04:45,041 --> 00:04:46,875
[YAMATOKUNI]
Those who run ahead of the pack

72
00:04:46,958 --> 00:04:48,750
are solitary.

73
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:50,375
But look to your side.

74
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:52,125
There are others
running with you.

75
00:04:53,291 --> 00:04:55,708
Rivals who share
the same determination.

76
00:04:55,791 --> 00:04:59,625
Striving to reach
that same solitary state.

77
00:04:59,708 --> 00:05:03,291
♪

78
00:05:04,875 --> 00:05:06,375
[KUZE]
Ushio.

79
00:05:06,458 --> 00:05:08,458
I'm grateful for you.

80
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:11,583
It was by my own will I decided
to fight you that day.

81
00:05:12,791 --> 00:05:15,250
I could see your soul, burning,

82
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:17,541
screaming to make itself known.

83
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:22,708
At that moment,
we fought at full strength.

84
00:05:22,791 --> 00:05:24,333
Just like now.

85
00:05:25,541 --> 00:05:27,083
[KUZE'S MOTHER]
His face.

86
00:05:27,166 --> 00:05:29,166
He's smiling.

87
00:05:29,250 --> 00:05:31,041
[MAN 3] Excuse me, ma'am.
Are you all right?

88
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:33,041
Yes. I'm fine.

89
00:05:33,125 --> 00:05:35,625
It would disrespectful
of me to look away.

90
00:05:35,708 --> 00:05:37,458
After all, I've been the wife

91
00:05:37,541 --> 00:05:39,583
of a yokozuna
for many years now.

92
00:05:40,708 --> 00:05:43,833
As a mother, it's an honor to
see how much my son has grown.

93
00:05:44,875 --> 00:05:47,708
[HINOMARU'S GRANDMOTHER]
Hinomaru! Don't back down!

94
00:05:47,791 --> 00:05:49,666
Your mother's watching!

95
00:05:54,958 --> 00:05:56,916
[straining]

96
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,541
Hinomaru can't afford
to just maintain his grip.

97
00:05:59,625 --> 00:06:01,791
The difference in size
will wear him down first.

98
00:06:01,875 --> 00:06:04,083
He's still tired
from the semifinal bout,

99
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:06,000
and there's his left arm.

100
00:06:06,083 --> 00:06:09,083
The longer this goes on,
the less his chances of winning.

101
00:06:09,166 --> 00:06:10,625
[HINOMARU]
Can I keep this up?

102
00:06:10,708 --> 00:06:12,541
His power's incredible.

103
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:15,458
Hurts so much,
I can barely breathe.

104
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:18,041
I need to do something,
but what?

105
00:06:19,125 --> 00:06:20,708
[groaning]

106
00:06:22,041 --> 00:06:24,041
[HINOMARU'S MOTHER]
Why is it you're doing sumo?

107
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:25,833
[gasps]

108
00:06:25,916 --> 00:06:27,291
[HINOMARU'S GRANDMOTHER]
Another loss, I'm afraid.

109
00:06:27,375 --> 00:06:28,666
Such a shame.

110
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:31,416
He did so well
in elementary school.

111
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,416
[HINOMARU'S MOTHER]
It's because of his height.

112
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:34,625
Huh?

113
00:06:34,708 --> 00:06:35,958
[HINOMARU'S MOTHER]
He's a good boy,

114
00:06:36,041 --> 00:06:37,708
so he'll never even think it.

115
00:06:38,875 --> 00:06:41,166
But his late father
and I are to blame.

116
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:42,750
We're the reason he's short.

117
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:48,500
I'm sorry I couldn't give you
a bigger body, my son.

118
00:06:48,583 --> 00:06:51,333
♪

119
00:06:54,041 --> 00:06:55,958
[HINOMARU]
Winning at sumo was a rush.

120
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:58,375
My mom was my biggest fan.

121
00:06:58,458 --> 00:07:00,541
She loved seeing me win
more than I did.

122
00:07:01,666 --> 00:07:04,750
She acted so brave
even when she was sick.

123
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:06,875
It made me want to please her
even more.

124
00:07:09,541 --> 00:07:11,000
It's all for her.

125
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,750
Still is,
even though she's gone.

126
00:07:16,208 --> 00:07:17,291
[HINOMARU'S MOTHER]
No.

127
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:19,333
Try to remember further back.

128
00:07:21,166 --> 00:07:23,875
Why are you doing sumo,
Hinomaru?

129
00:07:25,958 --> 00:07:28,375
[ANNOUNCER] Entering the
sumo ring from the east side:

130
00:07:28,458 --> 00:07:29,875
Yokozuna Yamatokuni.

131
00:07:29,958 --> 00:07:31,916
[CROWD]
Yokozuna!

132
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,291
Bet you want to be
just like Yamatokuni.

133
00:07:35,375 --> 00:07:37,750
That's why everyone else
signed up.

134
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:40,375
We're learning sumo
so we can be as cool as him!

135
00:07:40,458 --> 00:07:41,750
[HINOMARU]
That's not why I joined.

136
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:44,375
I want something different.

137
00:07:44,458 --> 00:07:47,750
[BOTH straining]

138
00:07:50,958 --> 00:07:52,625
Here it comes, Hinomaru!

139
00:07:52,708 --> 00:07:55,125
[straining]

140
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:58,500
♪

141
00:07:58,583 --> 00:08:00,250
[KUZE]
Great Serpent Cleaver!

142
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:02,250
♪

143
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:04,000
[grunts]

144
00:08:04,083 --> 00:08:06,500
[HINOMARU grunts]

145
00:08:06,583 --> 00:08:08,083
[gasps]

146
00:08:08,166 --> 00:08:11,875
♪

147
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:14,333
[HINOMARU] There's no
one reason why I'm here.

148
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:17,791
That's not why I joined,

149
00:08:17,875 --> 00:08:19,291
if you want to know.

150
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:21,500
After watching him,
I thought about how fun it'd be

151
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:24,125
to throw
a giant yokozuna like that.

152
00:08:25,958 --> 00:08:28,083
My initial motivation,

153
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:30,083
the feeling of losing,

154
00:08:30,166 --> 00:08:32,208
other's expectations,

155
00:08:32,291 --> 00:08:34,333
the time with my teammates,

156
00:08:34,416 --> 00:08:36,375
and for the memory of my mother!

157
00:08:38,041 --> 00:08:39,333
He's on fire.

158
00:08:39,416 --> 00:08:41,583
[HINOMARU]
The reason I'm here

159
00:08:41,666 --> 00:08:43,750
is 'cause I love sumo!

160
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:46,500
Is Hinomaru actually smiling
during a bout?

161
00:08:46,583 --> 00:08:48,625
♪

162
00:08:53,625 --> 00:08:55,041
Hmm?

163
00:08:55,125 --> 00:08:58,541
[grunting]

164
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:02,750
This is your shot, kid!

165
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:07,125
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
Close the gap!

166
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:10,625
When his upper body's extended,
come up from beneath!

167
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:11,875
[HINOMARU yelling]

168
00:09:14,458 --> 00:09:16,791
[ALL]
Push him!

169
00:09:16,875 --> 00:09:18,083
[gasps]

170
00:09:18,166 --> 00:09:20,583
[HINOMARU grunting]

171
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:21,875
He's almost there!

172
00:09:21,958 --> 00:09:24,333
[SHUNKAI]
It can only happen in a sport

173
00:09:24,416 --> 00:09:25,666
with no weight class.

174
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:29,958
The smaller contender rises
and invigorates the crowd!

175
00:09:31,625 --> 00:09:32,791
[grunts]

176
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:36,625
[SHIBAKIYAMA] He pulled back
right at the edge of the ring!

177
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:38,166
[YAMATOKUNI]
His spirit can't be contained

178
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:40,041
within such a small frame.

179
00:09:40,125 --> 00:09:43,750
This national treasure,
he's the future of sumo.

180
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:45,500
But Sosuke is no different.

181
00:09:45,583 --> 00:09:48,958
♪

182
00:09:49,041 --> 00:09:51,083
[YAMATOKUNI]
Witnessing size, speed,

183
00:09:51,166 --> 00:09:53,041
and unfathomable
physical strength

184
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:55,416
is a large part
of sumo's appeal.

185
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,041
That's a left underarm grip.

186
00:09:57,125 --> 00:09:59,791
[KUZE] Think you've seen
everything? No.

187
00:09:59,875 --> 00:10:02,333
The sumo my father and I share
is so much more.

188
00:10:02,416 --> 00:10:03,833
And you're about to witness it!

189
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:09,541
[yelling]

190
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:12,000
True Great Serpent Cleaver!

191
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:19,291
[HINOMARU]
Reverse Hundred Demon Takedown!

192
00:10:19,375 --> 00:10:21,208
They're throwing each other!

193
00:10:21,291 --> 00:10:23,541
Hinomaru was ready for it.

194
00:10:23,625 --> 00:10:24,916
[SHUNKAI]
He saw that coming.

195
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,750
[HINOMARU]
I figured you'd try to counter.

196
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:31,083
Only because I believe
in your strength!

197
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:42,666
[CROWD cheering]

198
00:10:50,083 --> 00:10:53,583
[straining]

199
00:10:55,416 --> 00:10:56,750
Hori.

200
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:58,500
-I owe you.
-Huh?

201
00:10:58,583 --> 00:11:00,583
I realize if it weren't for you,

202
00:11:00,666 --> 00:11:02,333
then I probably
wouldn't be here.

203
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:05,000
When it came to sumo,

204
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:06,833
I didn't know anything.

205
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:11,583
I made fun of the sport
because I didn't understand it.

206
00:11:13,458 --> 00:11:16,750
But when I'm this close,
there's nothing else like it.

207
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:19,125
The sound those
carefully sculpted bodies make

208
00:11:19,208 --> 00:11:20,666
every time they crash,

209
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,500
it's glorious.

210
00:11:22,583 --> 00:11:26,125
In a single moment, they execute
countless maneuvers.

211
00:11:26,208 --> 00:11:29,166
I used to think the belt thing
was embarrassing,

212
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:32,500
but I'm starting to appreciate
the aesthetic behind it.

213
00:11:32,583 --> 00:11:36,916
The more I learn about sumo,
the more I learn about him.

214
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,041
Just how strong he is.

215
00:11:40,083 --> 00:11:42,041
No matter how many times
he's knocked back,

216
00:11:42,125 --> 00:11:43,958
he keeps pushing forward.

217
00:11:44,041 --> 00:11:46,875
It entertains the crowds
and captures their hearts!

218
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:49,750
-It's love.
-[CHIZUKO gasps]

219
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:52,500
[grunts]

220
00:11:52,583 --> 00:11:53,625
For his style.

221
00:11:54,708 --> 00:11:56,791
It's love for Hinomaru's sumo.

222
00:11:58,041 --> 00:11:59,416
[KUZE]
Is this it?

223
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,083
I'm losing?

224
00:12:01,166 --> 00:12:05,125
♪

225
00:12:07,083 --> 00:12:10,333
♪

226
00:12:10,416 --> 00:12:11,750
[KUZE]
I refuse to.

227
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:13,625
I need to stop him.

228
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:17,375
Shake him back and forth!

229
00:12:17,458 --> 00:12:19,916
♪

230
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,041
[KUZE]
Am I'm actually fighting one?

231
00:12:22,125 --> 00:12:23,791
A serious sumo bout!

232
00:12:23,875 --> 00:12:26,250
♪

233
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:30,041
I feel so close to death,
it's exhilarating.

234
00:12:31,833 --> 00:12:34,458
Finally, my limits
are being tested.

235
00:12:34,541 --> 00:12:36,416
In order to beat him,

236
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:38,500
I have to transcend.

237
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:41,291
I can't simply imitate
my father anymore.

238
00:12:42,666 --> 00:12:44,250
I have to surpass him!

239
00:12:46,541 --> 00:12:48,791
I must surpass a god!

240
00:12:48,875 --> 00:12:50,083
Don't fall!

241
00:12:50,166 --> 00:12:51,375
Stay strong, bro!

242
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:53,666
[grunting]

243
00:12:56,583 --> 00:12:59,166
[YAMATOKUNI] There's no
forethought behind his actions.

244
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:02,375
He has something that can't
be taught in a training hall.

245
00:13:02,458 --> 00:13:05,916
This is pure instinct!
I get it.

246
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,666
So this is what it means
to drive each other higher.

247
00:13:11,625 --> 00:13:13,291
[KUZE]
Pulling Body Slam!

248
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:14,833
God Body Hammer!

249
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:17,875
[gasps]

250
00:13:20,041 --> 00:13:21,208
An illusion?

251
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:25,208
He only feels like a giant.

252
00:13:27,916 --> 00:13:29,125
[HINOMARU]
I've had to worry more

253
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:30,625
and work harder
than everybody

254
00:13:30,708 --> 00:13:32,500
because of how small I am.

255
00:13:32,583 --> 00:13:35,708
I've lived, breathed,
and dreamt about this sport.

256
00:13:35,791 --> 00:13:37,500
Thing is, because of my body,

257
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:39,958
I've been able to enjoy sumo
more than anyone.

258
00:13:40,041 --> 00:13:41,833
Mom, thank you for it.

259
00:13:41,916 --> 00:13:42,833
[grunts]

260
00:13:42,916 --> 00:13:47,208
♪

261
00:13:47,291 --> 00:13:48,625
[KIRIHITO]
His arm.

262
00:13:48,708 --> 00:13:50,000
[YUMA]
He hit his limit?

263
00:13:50,083 --> 00:13:51,750
[CHIHIRO]
Don't crap out now!

264
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:54,583
[KEI]
No. Not yet. Of all times.

265
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:56,208
[SHIBAKIYAMA] If this happens,
I'll never forgive

266
00:13:56,291 --> 00:13:58,041
the gods of sumo!

267
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:04,500
[yelling]

268
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:06,666
[HINOMARU] This body's overcome
every obstacle

269
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:07,958
that stood in its way.

270
00:14:08,041 --> 00:14:10,000
And I'm proud of it!

271
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:12,458
If the gods of sumo disagree,

272
00:14:12,541 --> 00:14:14,500
I'll throw them down too!

273
00:14:14,583 --> 00:14:16,166
Go, Ushio!

274
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:17,750
Take him out!

275
00:14:19,041 --> 00:14:20,833
Right underarm throw!

276
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:22,708
Demon Wheel!

277
00:14:22,791 --> 00:14:25,250
♪

278
00:14:26,375 --> 00:14:28,958
Take him out, Ushio!
Let's do this!

279
00:14:40,625 --> 00:14:41,875
[chuckles]

280
00:14:44,375 --> 00:14:45,958
[HINOMARU]
The name's Hinomaru Ushio.

281
00:14:46,958 --> 00:14:49,208
My dream is to become
a yokozuna,

282
00:14:49,291 --> 00:14:51,416
but first I need to be
the best high school wrestler

283
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:53,041
there is.

284
00:14:53,125 --> 00:14:55,875
[KUZE grunts]

285
00:15:04,916 --> 00:15:09,375
[SOBBING softly]

286
00:15:11,083 --> 00:15:13,333
-[REFEREE] East side wins!
-[cheering]

287
00:15:13,416 --> 00:15:17,375
-[CROWD cheering]
-[whooping and laughter]

288
00:15:20,166 --> 00:15:22,250
Listen to that
thunderous applause.

289
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:25,500
Yeah, but what's even
more beautiful

290
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:27,875
is the sight
of cascading cushions.

291
00:15:28,916 --> 00:15:31,625
[REINA crying]

292
00:15:41,666 --> 00:15:44,875
♪

293
00:15:44,958 --> 00:15:48,708
[panting]

294
00:15:48,791 --> 00:15:50,125
[YAMATOKUNI]
I'm glad it was him

295
00:15:50,208 --> 00:15:52,541
who defeated my son.

296
00:15:52,625 --> 00:15:55,041
I knew he would experience
defeat someday.

297
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:59,875
Now I can see what he'll do
the next time it happens,

298
00:15:59,958 --> 00:16:02,375
and how he'll win instead.

299
00:16:02,458 --> 00:16:05,666
♪

300
00:16:05,750 --> 00:16:07,958
[CROWD applauding]

301
00:16:08,041 --> 00:16:09,708
We can go.

302
00:16:09,791 --> 00:16:12,958
♪

303
00:16:13,041 --> 00:16:15,208
[applause continues]

304
00:16:15,291 --> 00:16:17,000
You really did it, Hinomaru.

305
00:16:18,125 --> 00:16:19,625
Wherever she is,

306
00:16:19,708 --> 00:16:21,375
I'm sure your mother
can hear the applause.

307
00:16:22,541 --> 00:16:23,875
[HINOMARU]
If I'd gone alone,

308
00:16:23,958 --> 00:16:25,666
I never would've made it
to this point.

309
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,833
I've been blessed
with strong opponents

310
00:16:28,916 --> 00:16:30,791
and mentors who tested me.

311
00:16:30,875 --> 00:16:33,708
♪

312
00:16:33,791 --> 00:16:35,250
And, of course,

313
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:37,416
I can't forget my teammates

314
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:39,500
and all of their support.

315
00:16:39,583 --> 00:16:42,083
[HINOMARU MOTHER] When
your dream finally comes true,

316
00:16:43,083 --> 00:16:46,708
I may not be there in person
to celebrate with you.

317
00:16:46,791 --> 00:16:48,458
But I promise,

318
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:50,750
I'll be smiling down
on you from above.

319
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:53,958
My dream hasn't
come true yet, but...

320
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,916
[NARRATOR]
Sumo.

321
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,416
Since ancient times,
warriors clad in mawashi belts

322
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:02,083
have waged battles
within the ring.

323
00:17:02,166 --> 00:17:03,416
[REFEREE]
Bow.

324
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:04,958
[NARRATOR] It is one
of the few combat sports

325
00:17:05,041 --> 00:17:06,666
without weight classes.

326
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:09,708
Thus, student wrestlers who are
heavier and larger in stature

327
00:17:09,791 --> 00:17:11,666
have a distinct advantage.

328
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:13,958
Among those giants,
there was one who desired

329
00:17:14,041 --> 00:17:16,541
to become a yokozuna
more than anything.

330
00:17:16,625 --> 00:17:20,125
Though his body was small,
it was sturdy.

331
00:17:20,208 --> 00:17:21,750
And above all...

332
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,166
East side wins!

333
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:25,041
[CROWD cheers]

334
00:17:25,125 --> 00:17:26,583
[NARRATOR]
...dignified.

335
00:17:28,083 --> 00:17:29,875
[ANNOUNCER] That concludes
the team tournament.

336
00:17:29,958 --> 00:17:32,458
Odachi High School wins,
three-two.

337
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,000
I just want to say,

338
00:17:36,083 --> 00:17:37,333
I'm so proud

339
00:17:37,416 --> 00:17:38,791
-of all of you!
-[HINOMARU] What?

340
00:17:38,875 --> 00:17:40,916
[REINA] I'm only crying
‘cause you started it!

341
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,541
Yeah, but I stopped.

342
00:17:42,625 --> 00:17:45,000
[REINA] Yuma, you're the best
in Japan too.

343
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:46,208
Thanks.

344
00:17:49,083 --> 00:17:51,666
[OZEKI] This used to be
a one-man sumo club.

345
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:54,916
Now we're the top
high school team in Japan.

346
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:55,916
I...

347
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:56,916
[sobbing]

348
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,291
I just wanted...

349
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:01,541
Seriously,

350
00:18:01,625 --> 00:18:03,500
I can't thank you guys enough!

351
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,583
[CHIHIRO chuckles]

352
00:18:06,625 --> 00:18:07,958
[CHIZUKO]
That's right.

353
00:18:08,041 --> 00:18:10,125
They won't compete
as a team ever again.

354
00:18:11,416 --> 00:18:13,833
And now, we wait to see
if Hinomaru's going

355
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:15,750
to the All-Japan Championship.

356
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:16,958
Yep.

357
00:18:17,041 --> 00:18:18,291
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
Nothing to worry about.

358
00:18:18,375 --> 00:18:19,583
[KIRIHITO]
It's been decided?

359
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:21,416
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
He did his part.

360
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:24,041
No way they won't take him
after all that cheering.

361
00:18:24,125 --> 00:18:25,791
-Right?
-Huh?

362
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:28,500
It's him!
Master Yamatokuni!

363
00:18:28,583 --> 00:18:30,458
How long has it been?

364
00:18:30,541 --> 00:18:32,250
Three years?

365
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:34,125
I'm honored
you remember me, sir.

366
00:18:36,541 --> 00:18:38,583
"Practice for three years
from now."

367
00:18:38,666 --> 00:18:39,958
Your words were an encouragement

368
00:18:40,041 --> 00:18:42,625
and allowed me
to endure until today.

369
00:18:42,708 --> 00:18:44,000
I'm in your debt.

370
00:18:44,083 --> 00:18:46,583
-It should be me thanking you.
-[HINOMARU] Huh?

371
00:18:46,666 --> 00:18:47,916
After watching your team,

372
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,541
I know the future of sumo's
in good hands.

373
00:18:50,625 --> 00:18:53,041
The pro league is very fortunate
to have you aboard.

374
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:55,750
Here's a bit of advice
if you want

375
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:57,625
to maintain
the same diligence.

376
00:18:57,708 --> 00:19:00,250
Go practice for three years
from now,

377
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:01,833
Hinomaru Ushio.

378
00:19:04,708 --> 00:19:07,125
You better not tell me
you're staying at Eiga

379
00:19:07,208 --> 00:19:09,375
because you lost
the team tournament.

380
00:19:09,458 --> 00:19:10,541
Trust in us.

381
00:19:10,625 --> 00:19:12,166
We'll win next year.

382
00:19:12,250 --> 00:19:14,125
You've got to keep
moving forward.

383
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:16,750
[scoffs]

384
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:19,750
[KUZE]
I feel disappointed.

385
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:21,125
Huh?

386
00:19:21,208 --> 00:19:23,666
It may be the only time
I get the opportunity

387
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:25,833
to experience
this kind of emotion.

388
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:28,666
To lose with teammates.

389
00:19:30,041 --> 00:19:31,708
I'm glad I came to Eiga.

390
00:19:32,875 --> 00:19:34,041
Yeah.

391
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:37,208
[ANNOUNCER] We're proud
to present this year's

392
00:19:37,291 --> 00:19:40,708
National High School Sumo Team
Tournament champions.

393
00:19:40,791 --> 00:19:43,125
From Chiba,
Odachi High School!

394
00:19:43,208 --> 00:19:46,333
[CROWD cheering]

395
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:49,958
[OZEKI]
Everyone,

396
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:51,208
thank you for your support!

397
00:20:16,791 --> 00:20:18,333
[CHIZUKO]
Ushio went on to compete

398
00:20:18,416 --> 00:20:20,625
in the All-Japan Championships.

399
00:20:20,708 --> 00:20:22,791
However, he lost
in the semifinal

400
00:20:22,875 --> 00:20:24,375
and took third place.

401
00:20:25,375 --> 00:20:27,791
His opponent, Tennoji,
was the champion,

402
00:20:27,875 --> 00:20:30,666
earning the right to become
a fifteenth-ranked makushita.

403
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:34,166
Wish your arm was fully healed
for our bout,

404
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:35,583
but, hey, a win's a win.

405
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:37,583
The count's two to one now.

406
00:20:37,666 --> 00:20:39,500
With me leading.

407
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:43,041
Get used to us trading victories
and losses from now on.

408
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:45,708
Don't forget, I'm a makushita.

409
00:20:45,791 --> 00:20:48,125
Still though,
sandanme's not bad.

410
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:49,166
Congrats.

411
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:51,958
Glad to have you.

412
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:52,958
Same.

413
00:20:54,166 --> 00:20:55,833
[CHIZUKO]
After the Inter-High concluded,

414
00:20:55,916 --> 00:20:57,625
Kuze entered the pro league.

415
00:20:57,708 --> 00:20:58,958
He joined in time to compete

416
00:20:59,041 --> 00:21:00,666
in the tournament
that September.

417
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:03,875
While you're only a sandanme,

418
00:21:03,958 --> 00:21:06,666
you don't have to worry
about size anymore.

419
00:21:06,750 --> 00:21:09,125
The first step to attaining
your dream is done.

420
00:21:09,208 --> 00:21:11,125
You're in
the professional league now.

421
00:21:11,208 --> 00:21:12,333
Welcome.

422
00:21:12,416 --> 00:21:13,625
Thank you, Master.

423
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,291
[CHIZUKO]
But...

424
00:21:16,375 --> 00:21:19,000
Ushio could only earn
his spot for one year.

425
00:21:19,083 --> 00:21:20,583
If he wanted to keep it,

426
00:21:20,666 --> 00:21:23,541
he would be forced to drop
out of high school.

427
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:26,500
And by extension,
that meant saying farewell

428
00:21:26,583 --> 00:21:29,125
to the Odachi High School
sumo club for good.

429
00:21:30,375 --> 00:21:31,583
We're proud.

430
00:21:31,666 --> 00:21:33,333
Ushio is a talented student
and athlete

431
00:21:33,416 --> 00:21:34,958
who'll go far in life!

432
00:21:35,041 --> 00:21:37,083
And his school will be cheering
him every step of the way.

433
00:21:37,166 --> 00:21:39,458
[laughs]
I'll do my best.

434
00:21:40,583 --> 00:21:41,916
[HINOMARU groans]

435
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,083
[SHIBAKIYAMA laughs]
Exhausted?

436
00:21:44,166 --> 00:21:45,750
It's gonna take a while
before you settle

437
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:47,416
into the swing of things.

438
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:49,875
It'll be even more difficult
once you're in the pro league.

439
00:21:49,958 --> 00:21:51,791
I know I don't need
to sugar-coat the truth,

440
00:21:51,875 --> 00:21:53,958
but your height's
gonna make you stand out.

441
00:21:54,041 --> 00:21:56,500
[HINOMARU] Yes, sir.
I'm on the same page.

442
00:21:56,583 --> 00:21:59,416
I also realize the attention
can be fleeting.

443
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:00,875
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
Hmm.

444
00:22:00,958 --> 00:22:03,416
Honestly, it's been like
a whirlwind up till today.

445
00:22:04,458 --> 00:22:06,583
The captain and Yuma
are studying for exams,

446
00:22:06,666 --> 00:22:09,291
and the others are off training
or busy living their lives.

447
00:22:10,958 --> 00:22:13,916
It's a shame I wasn't able
to give them a proper goodbye.

448
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,375
I hope they understand.

449
00:22:16,958 --> 00:22:18,500
Why am I worried?

450
00:22:18,583 --> 00:22:20,250
I'll do well in the pro league.

451
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:22,458
That'll be my way
of showing them how I feel.

452
00:22:22,541 --> 00:22:24,208
Just gotta grab my sandals.

453
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:26,583
Huh?

454
00:22:26,666 --> 00:22:27,958
What you got there?

455
00:22:28,041 --> 00:22:29,291
That a love letter?

456
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:33,916
The next best thing.

457
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:35,208
Excuse me!

458
00:22:35,291 --> 00:22:36,666
I've gotta take care
of something!

459
00:22:36,750 --> 00:22:38,666
♪

460
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:41,250
[panting]

461
00:22:42,625 --> 00:22:43,916
Uh!

462
00:22:45,250 --> 00:22:46,750
The captain's sumo ring!

463
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:48,166
It's been totally rebuilt!

464
00:22:49,166 --> 00:22:51,500
[YUMA] Thanks to Ozeki's
step-by-step instructions.

465
00:22:51,583 --> 00:22:52,625
Hmm?

466
00:22:52,708 --> 00:22:54,458
[YUMA]
Still was a pain, though.

467
00:22:54,541 --> 00:22:57,583
I never stopped feeling guilty
about it getting destroyed.

468
00:22:57,666 --> 00:22:59,125
I'm glad it's finally back.

469
00:22:59,208 --> 00:23:01,708
Before you go gallivanting off,

470
00:23:01,791 --> 00:23:03,458
help me break it in.

471
00:23:03,541 --> 00:23:05,000
-[KEI] Just to be sure...
-Huh?

472
00:23:05,083 --> 00:23:06,625
[KEI]
...we're not training.

473
00:23:06,708 --> 00:23:08,375
We're doing this for real.

474
00:23:08,458 --> 00:23:10,083
[CHIHIRO]
You better believe it!

475
00:23:10,166 --> 00:23:11,916
[KIRIHITO]
There's no point otherwise.

476
00:23:13,291 --> 00:23:15,041
This is our farewell present.

477
00:23:15,125 --> 00:23:18,458
Showing you the sumo club's
serious style you helped create.

478
00:23:18,541 --> 00:23:20,125
Think you can handle it?

479
00:23:20,208 --> 00:23:22,625
[chuckles]
You guys.

480
00:23:22,708 --> 00:23:25,083
This entire team's crazy.

481
00:23:25,166 --> 00:23:27,166
It's way too cold outside
for sumo.

482
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:28,541
[chuckles]

483
00:23:29,666 --> 00:23:30,916
[HINOMARU]
Maybe for anyone else.

484
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:33,291
But we're not like everybody!

485
00:23:33,375 --> 00:23:35,875
All right!
Who's ready to go first!

